Subject: [PATCH 4/4] wasm: strip SDL2 host, drive mcore directly from JS
Author: pi-extension-gba vendor-builder

ADR 0002 background (docs/decisions/0002-mgba-sdl-free-vendor-rebuild.md):
patches 0001-0003 left the vendored build structurally dependent on SDL2.
Even with -pthread dropped from the top-level flags, the SDL2 port
re-adds pthread internally, emitting memory.atomic.wait32 instructions
that block Node's main thread during callMain. Skipping callMain avoids
the hang but leaves SDL's renderer uninitialised, so the getPixelBuffer
pointer (vendor patch 0002) reads from a null outputBuffer.

This patch replaces the SDL2-based host wholesale. The new
src/platform/wasm/main.c:

  - Drives mGBA's mcore API directly: mCoreFind / core->init /
    core->setVideoBuffer / core->runFrame / core->setKeys /
    mCoreSaveState / mCoreLoadState. No SDL_Init, no
    SDL_CreateRenderer, no SDL_PollEvent, no WebGL.
  - Allocates a single 240x160x4-byte static videoBuffer; setVideoBuffer
    is called once per loadGame, after which runFrame writes into it on
    each JS-driven tick.
  - Re-exports the V7 JS API surface (loadGame, pauseGame, resumeGame,
    saveState, loadState, saveStateSlot, loadStateSlot, screenshot,
    buttonPress, buttonUnpress, addCoreCallbacks, quitGame, quitMgba,
    quickReload, bindKey, setEventEnable, toggleRewind,
    setIntegerCoreSetting, pauseAudio, resumeAudio, getVolume,
    setVolume, getMainLoopTimingMode/Value, setMainLoopTiming,
    setFastForwardMultiplier, getFastForwardMultiplier, autoSaveState,
    loadAutoSaveState, autoLoadCheats). Audio, rewind, fast-forward,
    bindKey, event-toggling, and core-settings endpoints are no-op
    stubs in v1 (SPEC §1 non-goals).
  - Re-homes the getPixelBuffer* exports from patch 0002. They now
    return the static videoBuffer rather than dereferencing an SDL
    renderer struct. Size/stride/width/height are constant (GBA).
  - Adds a new EMSCRIPTEN_KEEPALIVE runFrame() export. This is the
    synchronous frame-step the JS render loop calls each tick per ADR
    0002. mCore->setKeys is mirrored from the current keyMask before
    each runFrame.
  - Keeps main() defined (so callMain has a target) but empty. No
    SDL_Init, no timer, no futex wait.

CMakeLists.txt changes:

  - -s USE_SDL=2 -> -s USE_SDL=0 on both LINK and COMPILE options.
  - Adds -s USE_PTHREADS=0 (explicit guard against transitive
    re-inclusion).
  - Removes -s MIN_WEBGL_VERSION=2 / MAX_WEBGL_VERSION=2 (no GL).
  - Drops ../sdl/sdl-audio.c, ../sdl/sdl-events.c, ../sdl/sdl-text.c
    from the sources list.
  - Keeps ALLOW_MEMORY_GROWTH=1, ENVIRONMENT=web,worker,node,
    EXPORT_ES6=1, MODULARIZE=1, extended EXPORTED_RUNTIME_METHODS,
    RESERVED_FUNCTION_POINTERS, NODEJS_CATCH_* — all still required.

Apply with: patch -p1 < 0004-strip-sdl.patch
Base commit: thenick775/mgba @ be30a34e913da1ba7f040d3db4e10f700ce49f76
Depends on: 0001-add-node-environment.patch, 0002-export-getPixelBuffer.patch

